    "lyrics": {
      "text": "Jo-seph was a-mazed__ to see that which tran-scend-ed na-ture’s bounds, for with-out seed, thou,__ O Maid, didst both con-ceive and bear a Child. And he re-mem-bered the blos-som-ing rod__ of Aa---ron, the dew up-on the fleece, and the un-burn--ing__ bush which was not con-sumed, though it was all__ a--flame. Thus, thy pro-tec-tor and be-trothed___ cried, as he bare wit-ness be-fore the__ priests: A Vir--gin bear---eth, and af--ter child---birth, still re-main-eth a Vir----gin."
    }
  }
